The paper discusses the design of next-generation optical access networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper specifically focuses on the protocols and architectures used in these networks, which is related to optical networking (cs.OT) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses user-perceived performance, which is related to communication systems (cs.COMM). Finally, the paper proposes a research framework for the comparative analysis of different network architectures, which could be considered as an application of artificial intelligence and robotics (cs.AR).
